Here’s the next layer: a Reputation Ledger that updates each source over time based on how well its signals predict later outcomes.

This makes the governance system adaptive.

What it does
	•	stores source reputation stats
	•	updates predictive accuracy from real outcomes
	•	tracks consistency
	•	raises manipulation risk when behavior looks suspicious
	•	feeds those updated values back into governance

