What changed conceptually

Before:
	•	governance weights were mostly static inputs

Now:
	•	source credibility evolves from outcomes
	•	bad predictors lose influence
	•	stable good predictors gain influence
	•	expert/stake overlays still work, but they no longer float free from performance

That’s the start of a real decision ecology.

Next strongest move

The next upgrade after this is a domain-aware ledger, where a source can be strong in one domain and weak in another:
	•	u1 good at Pokémon taste
	•	weak at dating prediction
	•	expert1 high expertise in finance, not fashion

That would make the system much smarter without making it much more complicated.